Wannan yana nufin cewa bat ba zai iya zama mai ɗaukar kwayar cutar MERS-CoV kai tsaye ba.
A gefe guda, binciken da aka yi a Gabas ta Tsakiya ya nuna cewa raƙuman raƙuman sun nuna cewa sun kamu da kwayar cutar MERS-CoV, kamar yadda raƙuman da ke Gabas ta Tsakiya suka kamu da cutar a ƙasashen Afirka da dama.
An gano MERS-CoV mai rai, wanda yake kama da wanda aka gano a cikin mutane, daga hanci na raƙuman raƙuman, wanda ya ƙara tabbatar da matsayin raƙuman a matsayin masu ɗaukar MERS-CoV na gaskiya.
Ya kamata a lura cewa raƙuman da ke dauke da cutar MERS-CoV a gwaji ba su da alamun cutar, amma sun samu cutar sosai.
Abin lura ne cewa raƙuman da suka kamu da cutar ba su fitar da kwayar cutar ta hanyar numfashi kawai ba, har ma ta hanyar ƙwayoyin cuta, wanda kuma shine babban hanyar fitar da kwayar cutar a cikin bat.
Duk da haka, akwai tambayoyi da yawa, tun da yawancin mutanen da aka tabbatar da cutar ta MERS ba su da tarihin haɗuwa da raƙuma kafin bayyanar cututtuka, kuma ana iya danganta su da mutum-zuwa-mutum ko kuma hanyar da ba a sani ba, wanda ya haɗa da nau'in dabbobi da ba a gano ba waɗanda ke dauke da MERS-CoV.
Kwayar cutar SARS-CoV-2 ta yi daidai da kashi 96.2% na CoV RaTG13 na batsa, wanda aka gano a cikin Rhinolophus affinis na Asiya.
Kamar yadda yake a cikin SARS-CoV da MERS-CoV, bambancin jerin tsakanin SARS-CoV-2 da RaTG13 ya yi yawa don a danganta su da alaƙar iyaye.
Wannan yana nufin cewa batsa ba za ta iya zama mai ɗaukar SARS-CoV-2 kai tsaye ba, sai dai idan a nan gaba an sami kusan iri ɗaya da batsa coronavirus.
Ana ganin cewa dabbobi masu dauke da cutar SARS-CoV-2 na iya kasancewa a cikin dabbobin da ake sayar da su a kasuwar sayar da abincin teku ta Wuhan, inda aka samu mutane da yawa da suka kamu da cutar COVID-19, wanda ke nuna yiwuwar kamuwa da cutar daga dabbobi zuwa mutane.
Wasu bincike na kwanan nan da aka yi ta hanyar jerin nau'in metagenome sun gano cewa wasu ƙananan dabbobi masu shayarwa da ke fuskantar hallaka da ake kira pangolins (Manis javanica) na iya ɗaukar kwayar cutar beta-coronavirus ta iyaye, wanda ke da alaƙa da nau'in SARS-CoV-2.
Tsarin kwayar cutar ta coronavirus na sabon kwayar cutar ta pangolin ya yi daidai da SARS-CoV-2 da kashi 8592%.
Amma suna da dangantaka sosai da RaTG13, kuma suna da daidaito na kashi 90 cikin ɗari.
An rarraba su a cikin layin bambancin ƙwayoyin cuta guda biyu kamar SARS-CoV-2, a cikin itacen phylogenetic, wanda ɗayan yana da yankin haɗuwa da mai karɓa (RSD) wanda ya fi kusa da SARS-CoV-2 tare da daidaiton jerin amino acid a matakin 97.4%.
Akasin haka, SARS-CoV-2 da RaTG13 sun fi bambanta, duk da cewa suna da daidaito a cikin kwayoyin halitta.
A cikin binciken farko na pangolin marasa lafiya, an kuma bayar da rahoton gano ƙwayoyin cuta a cikin samfurori na huhu, wanda ya zama kama da SARS-CoV-2.
A wannan binciken, an yi amfani da wasu hanyoyin hadawa da kuma sarrafawa ta hannu don samun jerin kwayoyin halitta, wanda ya hada da kusan kashi 86.3 cikin dari na cikakken kwayar cutar.
Ba za a iya ware yiwuwar pangolin ya zama daya daga cikin dabbobi masu kawo SARS-CoV-2 ba.
Koyaya, saboda bambancin jerin tsakanin SARS-CoV-2 da beta-coronavirus na pangolin, dangin SARS-CoV-2, a halin yanzu babu wata hujja da za ta goyi bayan asalin kai tsaye na SARS-CoV-2 daga pangolin.
Bugu da ƙari, tazarar tsakanin SARS-CoV-2 da RaTG13 ta fi tazarar tsakanin SARS-CoV-2 da beta-coronavirus na pangolin da ke da alaƙa da SARS-CoV-2.
Ba a riga an gano hanyar juyin halitta na SARS-CoV-2 a cikin batsa, pangolin da sauran dabbobi masu shayarwa ba.
